OL,7,FMPs had been due to debate the
OL,8,FHillsborough Law this week but the
OL,9,Fdiscussion was pushed back until
OL,10,FMonday to allow the Government to
OL,11,Fpropose changes that might address
OL,12,Fcampaigners' concerns.
OL,14,FElkan Abrahamson, a lawyer for the
OL,15,FHillsborough Law Now campaign, said
OL,16,Fthe amendments allowed the heads of
OL,17,Fthe security services to make
OL,18,F"whatever decision they want" on
OL,19,Fwhether to disclose information and
OL,20,Fleft them "unchallengeable".
